massacre at Columbine High School and other tragedies in recent
years were aberrations, high school principals say that instances
of school violence have made them fundamentally rethink what it
means to be a principal. The principals say they are now acting
more like psychologists, drill sergeants, prison wardens, even
field medics than academics and administrators. By Paul Zielbauer.
