Buchanan seems to be sounding his patented campaign reveille as
much for himself as for his political ``pitchfork brigades.'' By
Francis X. Clines.
</P>
<P>
   FRISCO-BATHHOUSES (San Francisco) _ AIDS closed the bathhouses
here when the city tried and failed. It was 15 years ago, when the
epidemic was raging and bathhouses, as bastions of anonymous,
unsafe sex, were considered major contributors to the spread of the
disease. Now, in a city still in an official state of health
emergency after 26,000 reported cases of AIDS and 17,800 deaths, a
movement is growing to allow the reopening of bathhouses where men
can meet and have sex in private cubicles. By Evelyn Nieves.
