   HONGKONG-PIRACY (Hong Kong) _ Movie industry executives took it
for granted that that bootleg copies of the new ``Star Wars'' would
soon turn up here. But the warp speed with which it flew from
American cinemas to Asian streets _ two days _ has left people
whipsawed. And the movie doesn't even open here until July 1. The
knockoffs are a vivid illustration of how the purloining of movies
has been a flashpoint in trade relations between the U.S. and
China. By Mark Landler.
