Pedro Martinez is not exactly the wise old veteran offering the
benefit of his experience to the youth sitting at his knee. But
23-year-old Jaret Wright would probably do well to heed Martinez's
advice because he knows whereof he speaks. Wright, the Cleveland
Indians' hard-throwing pitcher, is fast gaining a reputation as a
head-hunter. By Murray Chass.
