<P>
   FBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead item: Mum is the word in Detroit.
Barry Sanders is not talking. The Lions have tried reaching Sanders
at his off-season home in Wichita, Kan. _ Coach Bobby Ross has
dialed for four months now _ but Sanders hasn't been picking up the
phone. Ross says he would like to hear from Sanders by Tuesday. The
Lions, Ross says, need to know what Sanders' plans are, especially
if he is going to retire, so the team will have time to acquire a
new big-time running back. By Thomas George.
</P>
<P>
