Jets have been listening to those who proclaimed the logical
successors to the Super Bowl in the wake of John Elway's
retirement. His goal for the preseason is to make sure that they
understand that it's just talk and that they must find a way to
quickly blend in the new players on offense and defense and get off
to a better start than they did last year, when they lost their
first two games. By Gerald Eskenazi.
