   FORBES-CAMPAIGN (Washington) _ Beginning next week, the Forbes
campaign for the Republican presidential nomination is opening an
usually early and heavy multimillion-dollar advertising offensive
nationwide, with an emphasis in primary battleground states, that
is intended to repackage Forbes. The message: Forbes, far from the
monotonous advocate of a flat tax who ran in 1996, has the breadth
and the personality to sit in the Oval Office.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 2 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
