<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO _ VENICE, Italy _ As the U.S.-led NATO bombing
campaign against Yugoslavia continues to escalate, the alliance
that President Clinton has tried to present as unified from the
outset continues to appear more and more frayed. The combination of
shuttle diplomacy on the part of the Russians and ongoing civilian
casualties has put more pressure on the alliance in countries like
Italy, which was never completely together on the air campaign to
begin with. Many NATO are flat out asking themselves, ``Why are we
still bombing Yugoslavia?'' Developing. (Holmes, Cox News Service).
30. WITH PHOTO. MOVED.
</P>
