   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   LOCK-BOX _ WASHINGTON _ As lawmakers left the Capitol for a long
Memorial Day holiday, Republicans boasted they had protected Social
Security from government ``raids.'' Democrats grumbled nothing has
been done _ or is likely to be done _ to reform the system.
(Lipman, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   Moved Friday.
</P>
<P>
   CULTURE-WARS _ WASHINGTON _ The rhetoric and budgetary salvos
have quieted since President Clinton appointed two Southerners,
Bill Ivey and Bill Ferris, to head the National Endowment for the
Arts and the National Endowment for the Humanities. In interviews,
the two talk about how they changed their agencies' cultural focus.
(Dart, Cox News Service).
</P>
