   Moved Thursday in (w) Washington and (e) entertainment
categories.
</P>
<P>
   LOBBYISTS _ WASHINGTON _ Some members of Congress never go back
home after they leave office. It's just too tempting to stay on
Capitol Hill and get rich. Former members are everywhere in D.C.,
often lobbying for the industries they worked with while in
office.Texans on that list include Marvin Leath, Jim Chapman and
Charlie Wilson. We'll find out what they're up to. (Moscoso, Cox
News Service). 30.
