r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RAC-HORSES-LADN     05-29 0471
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-HORSES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OLD TRIESTE LOOKS UNSTOPPABLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ Other than injury, nothing has stopped Old Trieste
lately.
</P>
<P>
   And after the 4-year-old colt's display Saturday, in which he
returned from a nearly nine-month layoff to win the $300,000
Californian by seven lengths, the question is whether anything but
injury can stop Old Trieste from winning the June 27 Hollywood Gold
Cup.
</P>
<P>
   While Old Trieste and jockey Chris McCarron led the entire 1[
miles at Hollywood Park, Californian favorite Puerto Madero ran his
second dull race in a row to finish third behind Budroyale.
</P>
<P>
   And 2{ hours earlier, a continent away at Suffolk Downs, another
presumed Gold Cup contender failed to impress as Real Quiet faded
to third in the $600,000 Massachusetts Handicap while Behrens and
jockey Jorge Chavez wore down 8-1 Running Stag to win.
</P>
<P>
   Hollywood Park hopes Behrens, the East Coast's leading older
horse, will travel to the $1 million Gold Cup.
</P>
<P>
   Real Quiet, the 1998 Kentucky Derby and Preakness winner, can't
be ruled out although jockey Gary Stevens offered ``no excuses''
for Saturday's defeat.
</P>
<P>
   And Puerto Madero is still aiming for the Gold Cup, according to
trainer Richard Mandella, who also plans to have Malek in the
1\-mile race.
</P>
<P>
   But they'll all have to catch Old Trieste, a son of A.P. Indy
who hasn't trailed in his past four races, winning by a combined
28{ lengths.
</P>
<P>
   Since leading but finishing 10th in the '98 Derby, Old Trieste
had won the 1 1/16-mile Affirmed Handicap and the 1[-mile Swaps
Stakes at Hollywood Park, and the 1-mile Del Mar Handicap at Del
Mar.
</P>
<P>
   Old Trieste's 11-race, six-victory career has been interrupted
three times by layoffs of three months or more, the latest because
of foot problems and a virus.
</P>
<P>
   ``There will be questions about whether he can go 1\ miles,''
said owner Gary Biszantz of Rancho Santa Fe. ``But I think what you
see now is a mature horse who has learned to rate (harness his
speed) a little bit.''
</P>
<P>
   Biszantz said he'll take nothing for granted in the Gold Cup,
even though the race is weakened with Free House and Victory Gallop
sidelined and Silver Charm apparently committed to a race at
Churchill Downs.
</P>
<P>
   ``They've lost some good horses,'' Biszantz said. ``But Behrens'
race today was very, very good. Real Quiet will come back, I'm
sure, with Bob (Baffert) training. And Puerto Madero _ maybe he'll
move forward off this race today.''
</P>
<P>
   In Saturday's other major race, the $500,000 Metropolitan
Handicap at Belmont Park, Behrens' Florida rival Sir Bear and
jockey John Velazquez rallied on the outside to beat Crafty Friend
and Liberty Gold as favored Affirmed Success finished fourth and
Cat Thief sixth.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
